commit.message:
Beta v1.2.3: Changed logo to "Blocky," with a small animation on the title scene. Added new scenes including a Game Over screen.

Only the Play, Main Menu, and Play Again buttons currently function. I
am currently working on the new scenes for the next update.
Beta v1.2.3: Officially changed name to Blocky. Added new logo and new buttons on main menu, and laid foundations for new scenes.
Edited README.md, added links.
Edited README.md with name Blocky.
Updated README.md with information about Blocky.
Beta v1.2.2: Refactored, organized, and cleaned up most of the code.  Also made the random generating of Enemy objects more random.
Beta v1.2.1: Altered the formatting of a few pieces of text, images, and game objects. Also working on deploying to Mac, the web, & mobile.
Beta v1.2: Added title screen music and in-game music for some character. More features will be implemented in the near future!
Beta v1.1: added an actual score during gameplay, some sound effects, and random enemy spawning.
Implemented a functioning high score, with accompanying text that is shown on the title screen. Next, scoring algorithm and enemy spawning.
Added a main menu / title screen to the game with "Play," "About," and "Exit" buttons. Now to augment the functionality!
Added collision detection on the boundaries of the screen to keep entities from going off-screen.
Implemented a player entity (green square sprite) that is controlled by the user with the arrow keys; also created an enemy sprite.
Added a simple static background sprite and made it display on the screen.
Created Unity project called BlockGame. Also created the basic structure of the game (added folders for better organization and foundation).
Initial commit
